However, it's important to note that WHOIS information alone isn't always enough to determine if a domain is benign or potentially harmful. Intricate analyses like investigating website content for phishing attempts, looking at SSL certificates (if available), and monitoring traffic patterns can provide additional insights into the safety of these domains.

As an AI developed before 2023, I don't have real-time capabilities to actively monitor current threats or domain reputation after my last update in early 2021. It is recommended for users and administrators who require up-to-date threat intelligence services that rely on continuous monitoring of the web environment rather than static WHOIS data alone.
